# Landing page

Before using Next.js APIs or file conventions, read the relevant guide under `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` (this project’s Next.js differs from public docs).

## Structure and composition

- Prefer a single route entry (`app/page.tsx`) that composes **named sections** (Hero, Features, Social proof, Pricing teaser, FAQ, CTA, Footer) as separate components under `components/landing/` or similar—keep `page.tsx` thin.
- Use **semantic HTML**: one `h1` per page, section headings `h2`–`h3`, `main`, `header`/`footer`, `nav` for primary links.
- **Responsive first**: mobile layout and readable tap targets (`min-h` / padding on buttons and links); use Tailwind breakpoints consistently (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`).

## Styling (Tailwind v4)

- Use **Tailwind utilities** and project tokens from `app/globals.css` (`@theme inline`, CSS variables). Prefer `bg-background` / `text-foreground` where those exist instead of hard-coded hex unless defining design tokens.
- Keep **dark mode** coherent with `prefers-color-scheme` and existing `dark:` classes where the rest of the page uses them.

## Next.js and performance

- Use `next/image` for photos and logos with explicit `width`/`height` (or `fill` with a sized parent) and meaningful `alt`. Use `priority` only above the fold.
- Default to **Server Components**; add `"use client"` only for interactivity (menus, carousels, form state).
- Set **`metadata`** (and Open Graph fields if needed) in `app/layout.tsx` or a route `layout.tsx`—titles and descriptions should match the landing’s real product name and value prop.

## Accessibility and UX

- Interactive elements must be **keyboard-focusable**; visible focus styles; external links use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` when `target="_blank"`.
- Don’t rely on color alone for meaning; provide **clear CTAs** with verb-led labels.

## Content

- Copy should be **scannable**: short headings, bullets where appropriate, one primary CTA per section when possible.
